{{Quote|The shuttle's destination was a previously unknown Rebel Hideout on Corellia.|[[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:AMJ">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Assist Mara Jade|Naboo}}</ref>}}
The '''Hidden Rebel Base''', also known as the '''Rebel Hideout''', on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] was one of the locations the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command]] relocated to after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] while looking for a more secret location. It was also used to recruit new [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel combatants]] and task Rebel spacers to assist with the Alliance's efforts.

==Description==
{{Quote|Pick up some supplies from the medcenter here in the base, and then proceed to each of the four guard posts around the base.|[[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:MS">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Rebel|Medical Supplies|Corellia}}</ref>}}
[[File:Hidden_Rebel_Base.jpg|thumb|left|280px|Aerial view of the base.]]
The Hidden Rebel Base was a hidden "command and control" center for Rebel operations.<ref name="Website">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=CORELLIA|text=Corellia}}</ref> It was located on the planet Corellia, in a remote area of the mountains known as [[Rhaler's Bastion]].<ref name="SWG:RH" />

The Rebel Hideout comprised several buildings, including the main command center and six smaller buildings.<ref name="SWG:RH" /> An underground detainment facility was located beneath the base and accessible though one of the smaller buildings on the surface.<ref name="SWG:Rt1IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the first Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> The base also contained two small landing pads for [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttles]].<ref name="SWG:RH" />

[[File:Hidden_Rebel_Base_turrets.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The defensive system of the base.]]
The base was surrounded by a tall wall and defended by several [[Laser turret/Legends|laser turrets]]. The Rebels stationed here were on constant alert for [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] troops and patrolled the nearby mountains.<ref name="SWG:RH" /> In addition, the underground prison was guarded by a contingent of Rebel [[Commando/Legends|commandos]],<ref name="SWG:Rt1IO" /> [[Rebel trooper/Legends|Rebel troopers]],<ref name="SWG:Rt2IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the second Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> [[Rebel Desert Trooper]]s,<ref name="SWG:Rt3IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the third Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> [[Rebel Prison Trooper]]s<ref name="SWG:Rt4IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the fourth Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Rebel SpecForce troopers]],<ref name="SWG:Rt5IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the fifth Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> [[blastromech droid]]s,<ref name="SWG:Rt1IO" /> [[Prison Battle Droid|prison battle droids]] and [[DZ-70 fugitive tracker droid|tracker droids]].<ref name="SWG:Rt4IO" />

==History==
{{Quote|Based on the intelligence you collected there appear to be six Imperial Officers being held at that location.|Mara Jade, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:AMJ" />}}
The Rebel Hideout was established by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]<ref name="Website" /> after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]<ref name="Insider" /> with the support of independent-minded [[Corellian/Legends|Corellians]] eager to oppose the Empire and provide a shelter for the Rebel Alliance.<ref name="SWG:RH2">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=loading|Rebel Hideout|Corellia}}</ref> The base was initially used as a temporary camp during the construction of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the planet [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]<ref name="Insider" /> but it then became the main Rebel base of operations.<ref name="SWG:RH" /> From there, Leia Organa made plans to take advantage of the Alliance victory at the Battle of Yavin.<ref name="SWG:RH2" />

[[File:Hidden_Rebel_Base_Corellia.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Rebel troops in the base.]]

After the Battle of Yavin, many of the heroes of the Rebellion worked from within the Hidden Rebel Base,<ref name="SWG:RH" /> including [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]],<ref name="Insider" /> Princess Leia Organa, [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], [[Qual'do Herm]] and the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]].<ref name="SWG:RTP">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=other|Rebel Theme Park}}</ref> They often recruited Rebel combatants to assist the Alliance in critical missions such as the rescue of the Rebel [[Spy/Legends|spy]] [[Simo Oron]],<ref name="SWG:TSCL">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Rebel|The Spy's Contact List|Corellia}}</ref> the infiltration of a [[Imperial warehouse (Riverlands)|secret Imperial research center]] on Corellia,<ref name="SWG:TIS">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Rebel|The Ithorian Scientist|Corellia}}</ref> or the [[Mission to Bela Vistal|recovery]] of stolen [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing starfighters]] from an [[Imperial Base (Corellia)|Imperial Base]].<ref name="SWG:SS">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Rebel|Stolen Starships|Corellia}}</ref> Another Rebel officer present there around the same time was [[Teslo Ten'Doora]].<ref name="SWG:BIttRB">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=faction|Rebel|Bring Information to the Rebel Base|Corellia}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], Imperial spy [[Finn Darktrin]] infiltrated the Rebel Alliance and visited the base, but decided not to reveal its location to the Empire.<ref name="TRoD">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: The Ruins of Dantooine]]''</ref>

Also in 1 ABY,<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> an Alliance shuttle crashed near the Corellian city of [[Tyrena/Legends|Tyrena]] during the [[Empire Day/Legends|Empire Day]] festivities. From data recovered in the crash site, an Imperial agent working for [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]] [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] discovered the base's location. The Empire learned that there was a prison facility within the base where six [[Imperial officer]]s were being held.<ref name="SWG:AMJ" /> Mara Jade then tasked a group of Imperial operatives to raid the base and rescue the prisoners. The Imperial agents did so successfully, and were awarded the [[Imperial Badge of Meritorious Service]] for this accomplishment.<ref name="SWG:Rt6IO">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Imperial|Rescue the sixth Imperial Officer|Corellia}}</ref> a large number of Rebel soldiers, [[Rebel pilot/Legends|pilots]] and officers were killed during the assault, including trooper [[Jorel Sherrol]],<ref name="SWG:Rt1IO" /> pilot [[Lancer Sair]],<ref name="SWG:Rt2IO" /> [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Caleb Shoma]],<ref name="SWG:Rt3IO" /> desert trooper [[Falen Buir]],<ref name="SWG:Rt4IO" /> SpecForce trooper [[Titus Froud]],<ref name="SWG:Rt5IO" /> and the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Chard Fristena]].<ref name="SWG:Rt6IO" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Hidden Rebel Base appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Star Wars video games|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:RH" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref>

In the game, the Rebel Hideout was the location of several famous Rebel characters who gave a series of quests to Rebel players as part of the so-called "[[W:c:swg:Rebel Theme Park|Rebel Theme Park]]."<ref name="SWG:RTP" /> This questline was completely revamped with the release of the "[[W:c:swg:Chapter 6 Notes for May 22 2007|Chapter 6]]," on [[May 22]], [[2007]],<ref name="SonyCite-Publish Notes – Chapter 6: Masters of the Wild">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67250&month=052007|text=Publish Notes &ndash; Chapter 6: Masters of the Wild}}</ref> but the update did not change anything for the base itself.<ref name="SWG:TSCL" /><ref name="SWG:TIS" /><ref name="SWG:SS" /> The underground detention facility was added to the Rebel base with the "[[W:c:swg:Game Update 11|Game Update 11]]," published on [[June 23]], [[2009]], and was present in the game during the [[W:c:swg:Empire Day|Empire Day]] events of 2009,<ref name="SonyForumsCite-Star Wars Galaxies: Game Update 11 Empire Day">{{SonyForumsCite|url=swg/posts/list.m?topic_id=940830|text=Star Wars Galaxies: Game Update 11 Empire Day}}</ref> [[2010]]<ref name="SonyForumsCite-Star Wars Galaxies: Game Update 17 - Empire Day VII / Remembrance Day VII">{{SonyForumsCite|url=swg/posts/list.m?topic_id=1100816|text=Star Wars Galaxies: Game Update 17 - Empire Day VII / Remembrance Day VII}}</ref> and [[2011]].<ref name="SonyForumsCite-Star Wars Galaxies: Hotfix 19.20">{{SonyForumsCite|url=swg/posts/list.m?topic_id=1219548|text=Star Wars Galaxies: Hotfix 19.20}}</ref>

